The paper deals with the problem of minimizing decoding delay in network coding over channels with erasures and intermittent feedback. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the formulation of a maximum weight clique problem, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of probability distributions and Markov chains suggests a focus on statistical learning (cs.LG) and possibly signal processing (cs.SI).
